{"can_edit": true, "from": {"name": "Ljubomir Ljubojevi\u0107", "id": "100000182091980"}, "subject": "What to do when Network drivers are missing  after installation", "updated_time": "2012-01-17T11:52:50+0000", "can_delete": false, "created_time": "2012-01-17T11:24:30+0000", "message": "<p>You bought new laptop, and during and after installation there are no recognized network interfaces. What now?</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>NOTE: I will expand this doc later.</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>1. log in into console as root</p>\n<p>2. run &quot;lspci -v&quot; and check for  &quot;lscpci -nn&quot;</p>\n<p>3. Find what kmod package in ElRepo supports it. link to DeviceID</p>\n<p>4. download and install via &quot;yum install &lt;file(s)&gt; --nogpg&quot;</p>\n<p>5. Use install DVD (Media repo) to reinstall kernel (so drivers are actually hooked to kernel).</p>\n<p>6. run &quot;system-config-network&quot; as root so the /etc/system/network file is created.</p>\n<p>6. Reboot</p>", "revision": "10150537889527728", "id": "10150537852397728", "icon": "https://fbstatic-a.akamaihd.net/rsrc.php/v2/y7/r/8zhNI-VGpiI.png"}